es? I’m not entirely sure.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_ZQbLpQJIhYvpRFExj27Hlaul|fc_01111c4b8c2cf06a0169f4332d0900819496d0d4421096f67a\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.apache.lucene/lucene-core/4.10.4/main/extracted/org/apache/lucene/analysis/tokenattributes -type f -name '*Attribute.java' -maxdepth 1 -printf '%f\\\\n' | sort | head -50\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 438, \"output\": 780, \"cacheRead\": 10240, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 11458, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777611552882, \"responseId\": \"resp_01111c4b8c2cf06a0169f4332141908194aa98344b47e58763\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.lucene:lucene-core:4.10.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T05-00-01-775579Z.log:575:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating class loading and metadata**\\n\\nI'm considering whether I need to add metadata for dynamic access coverage, as it may be useful for configuration. If the test uses a default factory, I wonder if the native image might fail due to reflection issues. It seems like I might need to use Class.forName for dynamic class loading. I think that if the TypeAttributeImpl is reachable via imports, I should be okay. Class.forName can load any class in the image, assuming it's registered.\\n\\n**Analyzing test implementation and metadata**\\n\\nI’m wondering if empty metadata might still allow existing tests to pass. I see that a static implementation uses findAttributeImplCtor for TypeAttributeImpl, but adding a default might complicate things by introducing MethodHandle without Class.forName configurations. I think I need to create a specific test class, AttributeFactoryInnerDefaultAttributeFactoryTest. To check dynamic coverage, I should use attributes not involved in other tests. Maybe I need to verify exceptions if an implementation isn’t available, which could require creating a custom public test Attribute interface.\\n\\n**Exploring Class.forName and test challenges**\\n\\nI'm thinking that the Class.forName call gets triggered here, but I have a test class that's a private nested type, which complicates things. The class name has a `$`, and if the implementation is absent, this directly leads to a Class.forName failure. I wonder if the dynamic access line is covered. It seems that dynamic loading of a nonexistent class in the native image should throw an IllegalArgumentException. But would this cause UnsupportedFeature issues? I’m not entirely sure.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_01111c4b8c2cf06a0169f43321f3fc819481f87e84cfbf585e\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9DMtiNu-VC3OffBr2QAJTeq5YqqoUc1fXzR4WKrwUzBL6xniHAR9KifK-m7fXiVONF_tPoUt2myB-99A7obbjtRWMvmJEMrjjlBnmw2SluPRCP6N6YU2Yr9eox4wrapf-ZcEirCaCAsHnb9_oece-lGUnYveZumH40dB8fKhSp4UVpgQA44mO5YRS6aeZS4ehaGYN1fskOxA4Y2ulvnjRrPYoeAjj5phWHx89lObibBpbQEuMjQbHY4jDqpoXphquNRgk1GXujFHA-K5OZ0elBdGaQ9LnE-b_aMBpu4t-eoew-Gl0v96i14iOMLGy-8hNjUabu3_6uMggcz7T_aaxmujIhkfcEhX2rzHKdTVRXQq_co9A9xhY30jRrpCDvnFDbinASORAS7PpH2vXv7i3ifVI5CMpCtPHTW6kAPcu6WXFBMY7f-8Fn0_imZAAu6BIXO2S3IGcQmBr6ZvYiHwM1ILt37KZQQrfD8we1iv5gHt9k4wGId7TSHnPnOlGy1OKGGD1659B8ZXWMrXOeI47VJYrCJWMnKVbkt9YHrfw6ejKa06YAY5AElWTQZrzqz9cX8rQpPHFEPFZxDeQUNkevmpmC8125g6iWWNh1VO1ee8bx5UeT5HGauvD7Q-Z_HZ7SVQxcWGdWisgHFfl0s13U053K6a9w6wKE4gvvbzYoUgOSgZrkd0Kkg67W1RwNe2szhxRCaT8tF6SDEfag6GInyzxKc75AQGUA6n_j7h9v_WSpK7w_ZRTMiBSDJHGNroPWXJWrY_0N_uCKY2nD1ofd7ZiwstMD6qRS-w_zuR44QQsgsnQgapqCUCYvolvfz6KsAXpHo4iYNAX6PUvmeDXjHYPFrLJCMHIhE7JJgcH638gRfvTiDep9TSqluzZ6E_cYQGB8cSfNFIeWr3o0dpZ_ZlV1vKUaDMKwi3CHxgxpf10XtOrZfd