 might complicate things by introducing MethodHandle without Class.forName configurations. I think I need to create a specific test class, AttributeFactoryInnerDefaultAttributeFactoryTest. To check dynamic coverage, I should use attributes not involved in other tests. Maybe I need to verify exceptions if an implementation isn’t available, which could require creating a custom public test Attribute interface.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring Class.forName and test challenges**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking that the Class.forName call gets triggered here, but I have a test class that's a private nested type, which complicates things. The class name has a `$`, and if the implementation is absent, this directly leads to a Class.forName failure. I wonder if the dynamic access line is covered. It seems that dynamic loading of a nonexistent class in the native image should throw an IllegalArgumentException. But would this cause UnsupportedFeature issues? I’m not entirely sure.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_ZQbLpQJIhYvpRFExj27Hlaul|fc_01111c4b8c2cf06a0169f4332d0900819496d0d4421096f67a\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.apache.lucene/lucene-core/4.10.4/main/extracted/org/apache/lucene/analysis/tokenattributes -type f -name '*Attribute.java' -maxdepth 1 -printf '%f\\\\n' | sort | head -50\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 438, \"output\": 780, \"cacheRead\": 10240, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 11458, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777611552882, \"responseId\": \"resp_01111c4b8c2cf06a0169f4332141908194aa98344b47e58763\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_ZQbLpQJIhYvpRF