ull native build. The issue arises because, in Native Image, calling `Class.getDeclaredFields()` on a test class needs the reflection metadata. I wonder if the agent needs to be running before native compilation to generate the necessary config effectively. It's safest to rely on JVM if there are uncertainties with field metadata in Native Image.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Assessing test execution and initialization**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking that if tests run in native mode after the agent, it could be fine. But there's a potential issue: the static initializer (clinit) may occur before the agent runs. If the class gets initialized at build time, then the Native Image might initialize `RamUsageEstimator` when creating the image. Consequently, the runtime tests wouldn't execute that initializer. However, the coverage report is generated on the JVM. If everything is done at build time, there shouldn't be any issues. I might need to import `RamUsageEstimator`.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_8BpskhZKfqtR8MaDU2eAez40|fc_0ae08bc83715e2ff0169f42ea8c1448194b4edc1d9c9e06a7e\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.apache.lucene/lucene-core/4.10.4/main/extracted/org/apache/lucene/util/RamUsageEstimator.java\", \"offset\": 461, \"limit\": 80}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 2809, \"output\": 1249, \"cacheRead\": 15872, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 19930, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777610392126, \"responseId\": \"resp_0ae08bc83715e2ff0169f42e9879888194bd82a0f7582eb4c7\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_8BpskhZKfqtR8MaDU2eAez40|fc_0ae08bc83715e2ff0169f42ea8c1448194b4edc1d9c9e06a7e\", \"toolName\