/lucene-core/4.10.4/src/test/java/org_apache_lucene/lucene_core/AttributeFactoryTest.java`\\n\\nWhat it covers:\\n\\n- Calls `AttributeFactory.getStaticImplementation(...)`, which reaches `AttributeFactory.findAttributeImplCtor(...)`.\\n- Exercises the resulting constructor `MethodHandle` through public Lucene API by creating a `TypeAttributeImpl`.\\n- Verifies fallback delegation when the configured implementation does not implement the requested attribute.\\n\\nI did not compile or run tests, per your instruction.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0599039c72060ae80169f432e0a05881969edf4d75375daba7\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 322, \"output\": 818, \"cacheRead\": 22016, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 23156, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1777611477790, \"responseId\": \"resp_0599039c72060ae80169f432d647fc8196b46f3ae62c4ab2f4\"}}\n1600:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Testing MethodHandle invocation**\\n\\nI want to test creating twice to confirm the MethodHandle invocation, not just finding the constructor. I see that it already calls create, which is a good start. Should we consider adding metadata reflect config? I wonder if the native image test might fail due to missing metadata. The repository tests probably use GraalVM Native Build Tools to run JVM tests for generating metadata. However, if I can't run those, the metadata folder is currently empty.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0599039c72060ae80169f432d6dccc81969f8305261f93a62a\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9DLgUFfnEnfD6rJ29_VZr33u_R37rgSrHRGpIs841hf2vOlhLxYRvxMLG64xiwPvrJWJguYS_DR0FSQCxoSyySZoismzUHKFqtO7kze-_-zLu